  "text": "Perhaps the most interesting open problem is whether there are faster algorithms to sample root-connected subgraphs or sink-free orientations. For spanning trees, Kelner and Mądry [CITATION_1] has shown that the random walk based approach can be accelerated to O(m √ n), which has kindled a sequence of improvements [MST15, DKP + 17, DPPR17]. This line of research culminates in the almost-linear time algorithm by Schild [CITATION_2] . It would be interesting to see whether these (such as graph sparsification and fast linear system solver) or other ideas can be used to accelerate cluster-popping and sink-popping as well.",
